---
[v1] arm64: dts: mediatek: add pmu support for mt7981

Add PMU (Performance Monitoring Unit) device node for MT7981b SoC. This
enables hardware performance monitoring support using ARM Cortex-A53 PMU
driver with GIC_PPI 7 interrupt, following the same configuration as MT7987.
---
v1: Add PMU support for MT7981b to enable perf hardware events monitoring.
---

Index: kernel/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7981b.dtsi
===================================================================
--- kernel.orig/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7981b.dtsi
+++ kernel/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7981b.dtsi
@@ -56,6 +56,12 @@
 		method = "smc";
 	};

+	pmu {
+		compatible = "arm,cortex-a53-pmu";
+		interrupt-parent = <&gic>;
+		interrupts = <GIC_PPI 7 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_LOW>;
+	};
+
 	fan: pwm-fan {
 		compatible = "pwm-fan";
 		/* cooling level (0, 1, 2, 3) : (0% duty, 50% duty, 75% duty, 100% duty) */
